list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: a hollow object, typically made of metal and having the shape of a deep inverted cup widening at the lip, that sounds a clear musical note when struck, typically by means of a clapper inside.
a bell-shaped object or part of something.
a musical instrument consisting of a set of cylindrical metal tubes of different lengths, suspended in a frame and played by being struck with a hammer.
(preceded by a numeral) the time as indicated every half hour of a watch by the striking of the ship's bell one to eight times.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: at five bells in the forenoon of June 11
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: tại năm tiếng chuông trong buổi chiếu sáng ngày 11 tháng 6

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: the cry of a stag or buck at rutting time.
provide with a bell or bells; attach a bell or bells to.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_en: the young men were belling and hobbling the horses before releasing them
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: Những chàng trai trẻ đang belling và lúng túng những con ngựa trước khi phát hành chúng

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: make a ringing sound likened to that of a bell.
spread or flare outward like the lip of a bell.
list_definition_mean.definitions_ex_vn: áo cô ấy thổi ra phía sau

list_definition_mean.definitions_word_en: (of a stag or buck) make a cry at rutting time.
